This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring October 10, 2011, as Columbus Day. The proclamation acknowledges the historic significance of Christopher Columbus's voyage to the Americas in 1492 and the impact it had on the nation. It also recognizes the contributions of indigenous peoples and the Italian-American community to American society. The proclamation encourages the celebration of Columbus Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, and directs the display of the American flag on public buildings.